1. PO notes are not actually being displayed in the PO details
   - Resolved: Added a visible “PO Notes” section in the purchase-order details modal when `selectedPurchaseOrder.notes` is present.
   - Verification:
     1) Open Restock → Purchase Orders.
     2) Open a PO that has notes.
     3) Confirm the notes appear in a blue highlighted block under the PO summary line.

2. modal behaviour needs to resize to fit dropdown boxes when they are expanded, right now when a dropdown box is used the modal hides it, the restock modals don't resize to fit the dropdown box into it, fix that with all those modals
   - Resolved: Updated `CustomSelect` to reserve vertical space in-flow while open (`marginBottom` equal to dropdown height cap), so the modal content grows/scrolls to accommodate expanded dropdown lists instead of clipping them. This keeps dropdown behavior consistent in restock/PO modals and avoids hidden options at modal boundaries.
   - Verification:
     1) Open restock/PO modals that include custom dropdowns (e.g., create PO/edit PO filters).
     2) Expand dropdown near the bottom of the modal.
     3) Confirm dropdown is fully visible (it opens upward when needed) and is no longer cut off.

3. on hold item orphaned from PO is showing unknown supplier, analyze if a schema update will be needed for actually carrying over the supplier link to the orphaned item
   - Resolved: No schema migration required. Supplier identity is already recoverable from `held_from_request_id` via `restock_items -> restock_requests`. Updated held-item queries to include nested supplier (`supplier:suppliers(id, name)`) and mapped that supplier into UI-held items, so orphaned held items retain supplier display and PO-linking behavior.
   - Verification:
     1) Put a PO line item on hold to orphan it.
     2) Open Purchase Orders → On Hold.
     3) Confirm held item displays the expected supplier name (not “Unknown supplier”).
     4) Click “Create request and link to PO” and verify open-PO selection is prefiltered by the correct supplier.
